   <indicator ascending="0" measure="1">
    <title>
     <narrative xml:lang="FR">Output Indicator</narrative>
    </title>
    <description>
     <narrative xml:lang="FR">Government Data Center is operational and 500 hundred institutional e-mail accounts are ready to use.
The Judicial Case Management System is operational.
The country has 4 full functioning courts.
Judicial organization laws are updated.
Civil and commercial  laws are updated.</narrative>
    </description>
    <baseline year="2020">
     <comment>
      <narrative xml:lang="FR">The country has no Government Data Centre and the authorities do not have institutional e-mail accounts. 
The country does not dispose of a Judicial Case Management System.
The country only has one full functioning court, in S&#xE3;o Tom&#xE9;.
The Country has an outdated judicial organization.
Civil and commercial laws are outdated.</narrative>
     </comment>
    </baseline>
    <period>
     <period-start iso-date="2021-01-01"></period-start>
     <period-end iso-date="2021-12-31"></period-end>
     <target>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="FR">By the end of 2021 :
- The country has a Government Data Centre to consolidate computational, human, and financial resources, currently highly fragmented and insufficient, allowing for investment planning, the exploitation of economies of scale and a reliable, planned, and monitored operation to support the digital infrastructure. 
&#x2022; The country has an Institutional E-Mail GOV.ST with a directory service and associated tools, for managing email accounts for all Public Administration officials and civil servants. 
&#x2022; The country has the design and normative framework of an Interoperability Platform to support an effective response to the diversity of requirements for integration, coordination, reengineering, design, maintenance, and evolution of existing and proposed services, the recognition and validation of multiple citizen identities, as well as to monitor and guarantee the reliability and scalability of the entire digital infrastructure.
- Access to Justice is increased, through legal consultations outside S&#xE3;o Tom&#xE9;.
- Sexual violence investigators benefit from specialized training.</narrative>
      </comment>
     </target>
     <actual>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="FR">- Due to the shortage of IT items in the market, there were delays jn the delivery of several components of the Data Center. Therefore, it was not possible to finish its installation in 2021. Everything is programmed to be done until the end of the first quarter of 2022.
- 500 hundred institutional E-Mail accounts were bought, but we are still waiting for the government, through INIC (its technological institute), to settle a problem related to the domain .st.
- The design and normative framework of an Interoperability Platform are technically done and ready to be shared with the government.
- Justi&#xE7;a + Pr&#xF3;xima brought legal consultations to the island of Pr&#xED;ncipe.
- 19 Sexual violence investigators benefited from specialized training.</narrative>
      </comment>
     </actual>
    </period>
    <period>
     <period-start iso-date="2020-01-01"></period-start>
     <period-end iso-date="2020-12-31"></period-end>
     <target>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="FR">By the end of 2021 the country has:
- a report, with statistical data, of the organics and activity of the Judicial and Public Prosecution Service Secretariats, for the last two years, in order to identify any weaknesses and enhance the development of these careers based on merit. 
- rehabilitated prison service building.
- Internal training of court officials.
- a report, with statistical data, of the organic and activity of the Courts and the Judicial Secretaries and Public Prosecutor&#xB4;s Office, for the last two years (physical check of all pending cases, segregating them by territorial and material competence, establishment of recovery strategies for pending issues, replacement of books registration by computer applications)
- a report, with statistical data, on the functioning of the Prison Establishment, for the last three years.
- a survey of the computer system (hardware and software) of the Justice System 
- the new prodoc on the Modernization of the Justice System for the period 2021-2023.</narrative>
      </comment>
     </target>
     <actual>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="FR">Everything that was programmed was done, with the exception of the prison service rehabilitation works that could not be completed.</narrative>
      </comment>
     </actual>
    </period>
    <period>
     <period-start iso-date="2022-01-01"></period-start>
     <period-end iso-date="2022-12-31"></period-end>
     <target>
